  "name": "True Love Story 2",
  "shortName": "true-love-story-2",
  "description": "<i>True Love Story 2</i> is a visual novel styled love simulation game where the protagonist meets many girls and at the end of each day can check the relationship progress which shows which of the girls like and which of the girls dislike him. The player moved to a new town and is living with his younger sister. The story progresses in a typical visual novel style where one reads onscreen text, talks to present characters and moves from location to location in a determined order. Free movement is not done directly on a map but is rather scheduled. During school and lunch breaks you can schedule places on school campus you wish to visit, and after school you can schedule the place around the town you wish to visit. Depending on place you visit, you may meet different girls, or if noone's there you will soon leave the place without engaging in any dialogue with anyone.<br><br>The game uses full voice acting for heroines and character animation when they talk. Going one step further, while walking sometime the background moves as well as the character you walk with, and distant character also appear smaller and in distance where you can see more of their figure. The story is split in three school semesters and each comes on a single CD-ROM and can be played in any order at the beginning of a new game. Initial setup lets you name your character and adjust some of your character's stats. Heroine galleries can be accessed via main menu but the CG event scenes there are unlocked as you play the game story.",
